      "name": "Verification method requirement for ASTM F1717 compression-bending validation",
      "description": "Per the project V&V plan (rev. C, section 4.2), the primary validation activity supporting the compression-bending credibility claim shall employ a controlled experiment in which the modeling team specifies specimen selection criteria, fixture geometry, load-application rate, and environmental conditions prior to data collection, ensuring that experimental inputs are fully characterized and traceable to FEA boundary conditions. This controlled-experiment requirement is mandated to satisfy FDA guidance on model credibility for implant structural performance submissions.",
